{{defn|Laws in some jurisdictions banning the production or sales of [[beverage alcohol]] in an attempt to prevent its use. These bans have been criticized because they create a black market, leading to corruption and violence. Nationwide, constitutional [[prohibition in the United States]], established by the [[Eighteenth Amendment to the United States Constitution|18th Amendment]] in 1920, ended in 1933, repealed by the [[Twenty-first Amendment to the United States Constitution|21st Amendment]].}}
{{term|term=Alice B. Toklas |content=Alice B. Toklas}}
{{defn|no=1|1=[[Alice B. Toklas]] (1877–1967) was author of an autobiographical book, ''[[The Alice B. Toklas Cookbook]]'', first published in 1954, which includes a recipe for "Hashish Fudge."}}
{{defn|no=2|1=A slang name for a [[cannabis edible]].<ref name="WeedBlog"/>}}
{{term|term=amotivational syndrome|content=[[amotivational syndrome]]}}
{{defn|A supposed medical syndrome of lack of motivation in cannabis consumers, which has been challenged.}}
{{term|term=anti-cannabis organizations |content=[[anti-cannabis organizations]]}}
{{defn|Groups fighting against cannabis legalization, or apologizing for harm caused by drug prohibition, including: [[Drug Abuse Resistance Education|D.A.R.E.]], [[Partnership at Drugfree.org]], and [[Smart Approaches to Marijuana|SAM]]. [See [[Prohibition of drugs|prohibition]].]}}
{{term|term=anti-cannabis propaganda |content=[[anti-cannabis propaganda]]}}
{{defn|Material prepared by governments, organizations, or the media, that is not [[journalistic objectivity|objective]] or uses loaded language to demonize cannabis or cannabis consumers. Early anti-cannabis [[propaganda]] includes the 1936 drug [[exploitation film]] ''[[Reefer Madness]]''. The 1980s media public service announcement ''[[This Is Your Brain on Drugs]]'' is an example of anti-marijuana propaganda.}}
{{term|term=April 20 |content=[[April 20 (holiday)|April 20]]}}
{{defn|International day for cannabis pride.}}
{{term|term=Assassin of Youth |content=''[[Assassin of Youth]]''}}
{{defn|1937 American [[Anti-marijuana campaigns|anti-marijuana]] propaganda film that depicts cannabis use leading to tragedies, and obscene, all-night parties. The film's title is from a 1937 article by U.S. "drug czar" [[Harry J. Anslinger]]. [See [[Prohibition of drugs|prohibition]].]}}
{{glossary end}}

