{{defn|1950s cannabis subculture, also called the Beat Generation. [See [[cannabis culture]].]}}
{{term|term=bhang |content=[[bhang]]}}
{{defn|A traditional edible preparation of cannabis, a drink. [See [[cannabis edible]]s and extracts.]}}
{{term|term=black market |content=[[black market]]}}
{{defn|Underground economy of illegal cannabis trade created by [[Prohibition of drugs|prohibition]]. The world illicit cannabis economy is estimated to be $141 billion annually, but the estimate might be low due to the clandestine nature of the trade.<ref name="Sullivan" />}}
{{term|term=Blue Dream |content=[[Blue Dream (cannabis)|Blue Dream]]}}
{{defn|A sativa-dominant, hybrid variety of cannabis also called Blueberry Haze because it is a cross between Blueberry and Haze varieties, with Afghani, Mexican, and Thai ancestry. [See [[cannabis strains]].]}}
{{term|term=blunt |content=[[Blunt (cannabis cigar)|blunt]]}}
{{defn|A cigar filled with cannabis often mixed with tobacco.<ref name=DEA>[[#DEA factsheet|DEA factsheet]]</ref>}}
{{term|term=bong |content=[[bong]]}}
{{defn|A water filter for smoking cannabis.<ref name=DEA/> [See [[drug paraphernalia]].]}}
{{term|term=Boston Freedom Rally |content=[[Boston Freedom Rally]]}}
{{defn|Annual [[cannabis rights]] demonstration held in Boston since 1989.}}
{{term|term=bowl |content=[[Bowl (smoking)|bowl]]}}
{{defn|no=1|1=The part of a pipe or bong that holds the cannabis.}}
{{defn|no=2|1=A slang name for a cannabis smoking pipe. [See [[drug paraphernalia]].]}}
{{term|term=Brownie Mary |content=[[Brownie Mary]]}}
{{defn|In California, before medical marijuana was legalized by voters in [[California Proposition 215 (1996)|1996]], Mary Jane "Brownie Mary" Rathbun (1922–1999) who was arrested three times for baking [[cannabis brownies]] using her Social Security to buy ingredients and cannabis that was donated, giving them away free to AIDS and cancer patients, was able to successfully defend herself in court, arguing that medical necessity outweighed the reprehensibleness of her actions.<ref name="Times2">{{cite web | url=http://articles.latimes.com/1999/apr/13/news/mn-26991 | title='Brownie Mary' Rathbun Dies; Advocated Medical Marijuana | work=[[Los Angeles Times]] | date=April 13, 1999 | accessdate= | author=Woo, Elaine}}</ref>}}
{{term|term=bud |content=bud}}
{{defn|The part of a [[Cannabis (drug)|cannabis]] plant that is consumed for its psychoactive properties.<ref name="Steinmetz"/>}}
{{term|term=budtender |content=budtender}}
{{defn|A point of sale employee of a cannabis retail dispensary.<ref name="Insider">{{cite web | url=http://www.businessinsider.com/what-is-a-budtender-legal-weed-2017-6 | title=What it's like to work as a 'budtender' in the legal marijuana industry | work=[[Business Insider]] | date=June 24, 2017 | accessdate= | author=Robinson, Melia}}</ref>}}
{{term|term=buzz |content=buzz}}
{{defn|Slang name for a pleasant euphoric [[Effects of cannabis|effect of cannabis]].<ref name="CheechAndChong"/>}}

