[[File:Cannabis indica Selkem.jpg|thumb|A cola]]
{{glossary}}
{{term|term=cola |content=cola}}
{{defn|Topmost flower bud on a cannabis plant.<ref name="CheechAndChong"/>}}
{{term|term=Compassionate Investigational New Drug program |content=[[Compassionate Investigational New Drug program]]}}
{{defn|After [[Robert C. Randall|Robert Randall]] became the first person to successfully use a [[medical necessity]] defense when he was charged with illegal possession of cannabis to treat his glaucoma, he filed a federal lawsuit, ''Randall v. United States'', in 1976, resulting in the federal Compassionate Investigational New Drug program being established, under President [[Jimmy Carter]], in 1978. At the program's peak, fifteen patients received cannabis. 43 people were approved for the program, however 28 of the patients whose doctors completed the necessary paperwork never received any cannabis and, under the [[George H. W. Bush|Bush]] administration, the program stopped accepting new patients in 1992.}}
{{term|term=concentrates |content=[[Cannabis concentrate|concentrates]]}}
{{defn|Products including budder, honey oil, [[live resin]], [[Shatter (cannabis)|shatter]], taffy, wax, commercially extracted from cannabis with [[supercritical carbon dioxide]] (''{{CO2}}'') or hydrocarbon solvents.<ref name=Cannabist/> [See [[cannabis edible]]s and extracts.]}}
{{term|term=connoisseur |content=connoisseur}}
{{defn|A particular marijuana enthusiast.<ref name="CheechAndChong"/> [See [[cannabis culture]].]}}
{{term|term=Controlled Substances Act |content=[[Controlled Substances Act]]}}
{{defn|U.S. federal law enacted by President [[Richard Nixon]] in 1970 to replace [[Harry Anslinger]]'s [[1937 Marihuana Tax Act]] that was ruled unconstitutional by the [[Supreme Court of the United States|Supreme Court]]. The Controlled Substances Act created a list of five Schedules, and placed cannabis alongside [[codeine]] and [[heroin]] in [[List of Schedule I drugs (US)|Schedule I]], the most restrictive classification. [See [[Prohibition of drugs|prohibition]].]}}
{{term|term=cottonmouth |content=cottonmouth}}
{{defn|Slang name for a dry mouth caused by smoking or vaporizing cannabis or cannabis extracts.<ref name="CheechAndChong"/> [See [[effects of cannabis]].]}}

