== D ==
[[File:Bong glas.jpg|thumb|upright=0.50|Drug paraphernalia: A glass bong]]
{{glossary}}
{{term|term=dab |content=dab}}
{{defn|Slang name for [[hash oil]], a resin extracted from cannabis.<ref name=DEA/> [See [[cannabis edible]]s and extracts.]}}
{{term|term=dabbing |content=dabbing}}
{{defn|A slang term for smoking or vape-ing [[hash oil]], or "dabs," extracted from cannabis.<ref name=DEA/> [See [[cannabis consumption]].]}}
{{term|term=dab rig |content=dab rig}}
{{defn|[[Water pipe percolator|Water pipe]] device for vaporizing [[hash oil]].<ref name="DenverPostCannabist"/> [See [[drug paraphernalia]].]}}
{{term|term=dagga |content=dagga}}
{{defn|Afrikaans word for [[cannabis]], derived from the Khoikhoi ''dachab''.<ref name="WeedBlog"/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.etymonline.com/index.php?term=dagga|title=Online Etymology Dictionary|accessdate=}}</ref>}}
{{term|term=dank |content=dank}}
{{defn|A slang word for high quality [[cannabis]].<ref name="Steinmetz"/>}}
{{term|term=D.A.R.E. |content=[[Drug Abuse Resistance Education|D.A.R.E.]]}}
{{defn|US and UK government anti-freedom [[indoctrination]] program aimed at elementary school fourth through sixth-graders, instituted by [[LAPD]] chief [[Daryl Gates]] in 1983. The Drug Abuse Resistance Education program is costly, and is criticized for pushing out science-based health education. Other criticisms of the program include its ineffectiveness, and its training of children to be police [[informant]]s. [See [[anti-cannabis organizations]].]}}
{{term|term=DEA or Drug Enforcement Administration |content=[[DEA]] or [[Drug Enforcement Administration]]}}
{{defn|U.S. federal agency formed in 1970 by the establishment of President [[Richard Nixon]]'s [[Controlled Substances Act]]. The organization is criticized for being unaccountable to any authority, and for self-serving acts including blocking the removal of cannabis from Schedule I. [See [[Prohibition of drugs|prohibition]].]}}
{{term|term=decriminalization |content=[[decriminalization]]}}
{{defn|The lessening of [[Civil penalty|criminal penalties]] in relation to consumption of cannabis, reflecting changing social and moral views. [See [[Reform movement|reform]].]}}
{{term|term=ditch weed or ditchweed |content=[[ditch weed]] or [[ditchweed]]}}
{{defn|no=1|1=Slang term describing [[feral cannabis]].}}
{{defn|no=2|1=A slang name for poor-quality marijuana.<ref name="WeedBlog"/>}}
{{term|term=doobie |content=[[doobie]]}}
{{defn|A slang word for cannabis cigarette.<ref name="Steinmetz"/> [See [[Joint (cannabis)|joint]].]}}
{{term|term=dronabinol |content=[[dronabinol]]}}
{{defn|Synthetically manufactured [[tetrahydrocannabinol]] (THC), sold under the brand names Marinol and Syndros, produced by Insys Therapeutics and Solvay Pharmaceuticals, marketed legally in the United States under Schedule III of the Controlled Substances Act, though natural THC is banned under Schedule I.}}
{{term|term=drug czar or Drug Czar |content=[[drug czar]] or [[Drug czar|Drug Czar]]}}
{{defn|A person put in charge of drug policy for some region, usually at a national level (US or UK).}}
