{{term|term=Indian Hemp Drugs Commission |content=[[Indian Hemp Drugs Commission]]}}
{{defn|British and Indian government 3,281-page 1894 study of cannabis use in India that found there are no ill effects from moderate cannabis usage, and it may be beneficial medically. However the report concluded that excessive consumption is an indication of moral weakness or depravity.}}
{{term|term=indoctrination |content=[[indoctrination]]}}
{{defn|Process of inculcating a person with ideas, attitudes, or cognitive strategies, distinguished from education on the basis that the indoctrinated person is expected not to question or critically examine the doctrine they have learned. [See [[anti-cannabis propaganda]].]}}
{{term|term=industrial hemp |content=[[industrial hemp]]}}
{{defn|[[Cannabis]] cultivated to make products that are non-psychoactive.}}
{{term|term=informant |content=[[informant]]}}
{{defn|A word used to describe an undercover police informant, narcotics agent, or snitch.}}
{{term|term=initiative |content=[[initiative]]}}
{{defn|Citizens' initiatives are a method, allowed in some jurisdictions, to put a law up for popular vote by getting petitions signed by a certain minimum number of registered voters. Popular initiatives are allowed in twenty-one U.S. states.}}
