{{defn|A pipe for smoking cannabis. [See [[drug paraphernalia]].]}}
{{term|term=Operation Green Merchant |content=[[Operation Green Merchant]]}}
{{defn|[[Reagan]]-era DEA investigation primarily targeting advertisers in ''[[High Times]]'' and ''Sinsemilla Tips'' magazines. [See [[Prohibition of drugs|prohibition]].]}}
{{term|term=Operation Pipe Dreams |content=[[Operation Pipe Dreams]]}}
{{defn|Code-name for a 2003 U.S. [[Drug Enforcement Administration]] investigation targeting businesses selling [[Bowl (smoking)|cannabis pipe]]s and [[bong]]s. Hundreds of businesses and homes were raided during the operation. Fifty-five people were charged with trafficking of illegal drug paraphernalia, including actor [[Tommy Chong]], who was sentenced to 9 months in federal prison for financing and promoting a glass shop. Operation Pipe Dreams was estimated to have cost more than $12 million. [See [[Prohibition of drugs|prohibition]].]}}

