The '''Kararao''' are a tribe of the [[Kayapo people|Kayapo nation]] of [[Brazil]].<ref>[http://lucy.ukc.ac.uk/Sonja/RF/Ukpr/Report34.htm UNCONTACTED ETHNIC GROUPS]. Retrieved 2007-03-06.</ref>  As of 2004, contacted Kararao numbered only 29 individuals and a further 50 or so remain [[uncontacted peoples|uncontacted]].  The Kararao live in the Terra Indigena Kararahô in [[Pará]] (Area-3308.37&nbsp;km²).

